   =20
      Is ChatGPT securities fraud?
   =20
 =20

I suppose we will end up finding a number of answers to that question. Will=
 some ChatGPT-style large language model manage to do some insider trading?=
 Will it, like, ingest some corpus of data that includes inside information=
, and then use it to answer questions like =E2=80=9Cwhich stocks should I b=
uy?=E2=80=9D Will some big company=E2=80=99s corporate development departme=
nt use the model to answer questions like =E2=80=9Cshould we buy Company X =
and what price should we pay for it,=E2=80=9D and will the developers of th=
e model use that information nefariously? Will the model itself become sent=
ient, get a Robinhood account and use that information nefariously? Etc.
Or I mean will someone ask ChatGPT a question like =E2=80=9Cwhat companies =
are frauds,=E2=80=9D and ChatGPT will cheerfully and confidently say =E2=80=
=9Coh Company Y is a total fraud, their revenues are super inflated,=E2=80=
=9D and then people will short the stock, and then it will turn out that Co=
mpany Y is fine and ChatGPT is just really good at confidently making stuff=
 up? Is that securities fraud? By whom? (Or: Ask =E2=80=9Cwhat stocks are g=
ood,=E2=80=9D ChatGPT says =E2=80=9CCompany Z is great, they have found a c=
ure for cancer and their revenue will double,=E2=80=9D people buy the stock=
, it was all made up.) Will sell-side analysts or journalists use ChatGPT t=
o do their work, and will ChatGPT introduce market-moving factual mistakes?=
=C2=A0
Lots of fun possibilities. But the most immediate way in which ChatGPT is g=
oing to be securities fraud is the usual =E2=80=9Ceverything is securities =
fraud=E2=80=9D way:
=09ChatGPT is going to be disruptive to some number of businesses and indus=
tries.=09Some companies will lose money because ChatGPT disrupts their busi=
ness.=09This will be bad, for them, and their stocks will drop.=09Every bad=
 thing that happens to a public company can be characterized as securities =
fraud: =E2=80=9CYou didn=E2=80=99t sufficiently warn us about the bad thing=
, so we bought the stock thinking it was good, but then the bad thing happe=
ned and the stock dropped, so we were defrauded.=E2=80=9D

ChatGPT risk factors are  starting to be included in securities=C2=A0offeri=
ng documents, and the   risks are starting to be realized:

Chegg Inc. plummeted 42% after warning that the ChatGPT tool is threatening=
 growth of its homework-help services, one of the most notable market react=
ions yet to signs that generative AI is upending industries.
The company, which offers online guidance for students taking tests and wri=
ting essays, also gave revenue and profit forecasts for the current quarter=
 that fell well short of analysts=E2=80=99 estimates. Chegg makes much of i=
ts money from subscriptions, which start at $15.95 a month, a revenue sourc=
e that=E2=80=99s in peril if students see AI chatbots as an alternative to =
paying.
The impact of ChatGPT, an OpenAI tool that surged in popularity last year, =
began to be felt this spring, Chief Executive Officer Dan Rosensweig said i=
n prepared remarks accompanying Chegg=E2=80=99s first-quarter earnings Mond=
ay.

And I tell you what, when I see that a public company has=C2=A0announced ba=
d news and its stock dropped, I look for the lawsuits. We are early yet =E2=
=80=94=C2=A0the stock dropped=C2=A0yesterday=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0but lawyer=
s move fast; I have not yet seen any lawsuits filed, but at least  two law =
 firms have announced =E2=80=9Cinvestigations=E2=80=9D of Chegg and are loo=
king for clients.
At this point the lawsuits seem a bit far-fetched: =E2=80=9CYou should have=
 warned us months ago that artificial intelligence would hurt your business=
=E2=80=9D is unfair given how quickly ChatGPT has exploded from nowhere to =
become a cultural and business phenomenon. But now everyone is on notice! I=
f you are not warning your shareholders now=C2=A0about how AI could hurt yo=
ur business, and then it does hurt your business, you=E2=80=99re gonna get =
sued.

